Interface HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<K extends Comparable,V,H extends HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<K,V,H>>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Comparable, HierarchyNode<com.davidsoergel.dsutils.collections.OrderedPair<K,V>,H>, Iterable<H>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ExtendedHierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<K,V,H>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractExtendedHierarchicalTypedPropertyNode, AbstractHierarchicalTypedPropertyNode, BasicHierarchicalTypedPropertyNode, ExtendedHierarchicalTypedPropertyNodeImpl, SerializableHierarchicalTypedPropertyNode

    public interface HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<K extends Comparable,V,H extends HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode<K,V,H>>
extends Comparable, HierarchyNode<com.davidsoergel.dsutils.collections.OrderedPair<K,V>,H>
    Describes a node in a tree containing a key-value pair (at this node) and a set of children. The types of both the key and the value are generic. The children can be retrieved by key, Map-style. Also stores various flags (e.g., nullable, editable, etc.) to support the @Property framework.
    Version:
    $Id: HierarchicalTypedPropertyNode.java 250 2009-07-29 01:05:06Z soergel $
    Author:
